# Environment Variables Reference

## Frontend Environment Variables

### Development (.env or src/environments/environment.ts)
```
# API Configuration
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
```

### Production (Netlify)
```
# Set these in Netlify UI (Settings > Build & Deploy > Environment)

# Option 1: Using relative path (requires reverse proxy)
API_BASE_URL=/api

# Option 2: Using separate domain
API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/api

# Option 3: Using environment-specific URL
API_BASE_URL=https://api-prod.herokuapp.com/api
```

---

## Backend Environment Variables

### Development
No environment variables required - all configured in `application.properties`

### Production (Heroku/Cloud Platform)

```bash
# Server Configuration
SERVER_PORT=8080
JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx512m

# Database Configuration
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://db-server:3306/findit
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=db_user
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=db_password
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=validate

# File Upload Configuration
APP_UPLOAD_DIR=/tmp/uploads
MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE=52428800  # 50MB

# CORS Configuration
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://example.netlify.app,https://www.example.com

# AWS S3 Configuration (if using S3 for image storage)
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_BUCKET=findit-images
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key

# Cloudinary Configuration (if using Cloudinary for images)
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your-api-key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your-api-secret

# Firebase Configuration (if using Firebase Storage)
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=your-private-key
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=your-client-email

# Logging
LOGGING_LEVEL_ROOT=INFO
LOGGING_LEVEL_COM_EXAMPLE=DEBUG
```

---

## Netlify Configuration

### Build Environment Variables

Set in Netlify UI or netlify.toml:

```bash
# Required
NODE_ENV=production
NODE_VERSION=18.17.0

# Optional
DEPLOY_BRANCH=main
PUBLISH_DIR=dist/lostfound-frontend
COMMAND=npm run build

# API Configuration
API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/api
```

### Example netlify.toml Configuration

```toml
[build]
  command = "npm run build"
  publish = "dist/lostfound-frontend"
  environment = { NODE_VERSION = "18.17.0" }

[build.environment]
  NODE_ENV = "production"
  API_BASE_URL = "https://api.example.com/api"
```

---

## Database Configuration

### Development (H2 In-Memory)
*No setup required - automatic*

### Production (PostgreSQL)

```bash
# Set these environment variables on your backend server

SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/findit
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=postgres
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=your-password
SPRING_JPA_DATABASE_PLATFORM=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=validate
```

### Production (MySQL)

```bash
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/findit?useSSL=true&serverTimezone=UTC
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=root
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=your-password
SPRING_JPA_DATABASE_PLATFORM=org.hibernate.dialect.MySQL8Dialect
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=validate
```

---

## Local Development .env File

Create `.env` in project root (for frontend):

```bash
# Frontend API Configuration
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
NODE_ENV=development

# Optional: Debugging
DEBUG=*
```

Create `backend/.env` or use `application-dev.properties`:

```bash
# Backend Configuration
SERVER_PORT=8080
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=dev
```

---

## Environment-Specific Configurations

### Local Development
```
Frontend: http://localhost:4200
Backend: http://localhost:8080
Database: H2 (embedded)
Storage: Local filesystem
```

### Staging (Netlify Preview)
```
Frontend: https://staging--findit.netlify.app
Backend: https://api-staging.example.com
Database: PostgreSQL (staging server)
Storage: S3 or Cloudinary
```

### Production
```
Frontend: https://findit.example.com
Backend: https://api.example.com
Database: PostgreSQL or MySQL (production server)
Storage: S3 or Cloudinary (CDN)
```

