## AWS Configuration

### EC2 or Lambda Environment

```bash
# Application
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Database
MYSQL_HOST=your-rds-instance.amazonaws.com
MYSQL_PORT=3306
MYSQL_DATABASE=findit
MYSQL_USER=admin
MYSQL_PASSWORD=your-password

# S3
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_BUCKET=findit-uploads
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret

# Firebase (optional alternative)
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=findit-project
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=...

# Cloudinary (optional alternative)
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=...
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=...
```

---

## Google Cloud Configuration

### Cloud Run

```bash
PORT=8080
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@cloudsql-proxy/dbname
CLOUD_SQL_CONNECTION_NAME=project:region:instance-name
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/secrets/firebase-key.json
```

### App Engine

```yaml
# app.yaml
env: standard
runtime: java17

env_variables:
  DATABASE_URL: "postgresql://..."
  GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT: "your-project"
  STORAGE_BUCKET: "your-bucket"
```

---

## Azure Configuration

### App Service

```bash
# Set via Azure Portal or CLI
az webapp config appsettings set \
  --resource-group myGroup \
  --name myAPI \
  --settings \
    WEBSITES_PORT=8080 \
    DATABASE_URL=... \
    AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=...
```

---

## Secrets Management

### Do NOT commit secrets to Git

```bash
# .gitignore
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
secrets/
.secrets/
```

### Secure Secret Storage

**Option 1: Use Platform's Secret Manager**
- Netlify: Settings > Build & Deploy > Environment
- Heroku: `heroku config:set KEY=VALUE`
- Railway: Dashboard > Environment
- Azure: Key Vault
- AWS: Secrets Manager

**Option 2: Use Local .env (Development Only)**
```bash
# Create .env (add to .gitignore)
DATABASE_PASSWORD=secret123

# Load in your app
require('dotenv').config();
const dbPass = process.env.DATABASE_PASSWORD;
```

**Option 3: Environment-Specific Files**
```bash
application-prod.properties      # Git-ignored
application-staging.properties   # Git-ignored
application-dev.properties       # Committed (with safe defaults)
```

---

## Validation Checklist

Before deploying to production:

- [ ] All environment variables set on target platform
- [ ] Database credentials are secure
- [ ] API endpoints are HTTPS
- [ ] CORS origins are restricted
- [ ] Secrets are not in code
- [ ] .env files are in .gitignore
- [ ] File storage is configured (S3/Cloudinary)
- [ ] Logging is enabled
- [ ] Error monitoring is configured
- [ ] Backups are configured

---

## Troubleshooting

### "Connection refused" error
- Check DATABASE_URL is correct
- Verify database server is running
- Check firewall rules

### API returns 404
- Check API_BASE_URL is correct
- Verify backend is running
- Check CORS configuration

### Images not loading
- Check file storage path exists
- Verify S3/Cloudinary credentials
- Check file permissions

### Out of memory errors
- Increase JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx memory
- Check for memory leaks
- Optimize database queries

